<TITLE> SQ Chowdhury taken back to Kashimpur prison </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 27 (bdnews24.com)  Former prime minister Khaleda Zia's parliamentary affairs adviser Salahuddin Qader Chowdhury was transferred from Ibrahim Cardiac Hospital and Research Institute (ICHRI) to Kashimpur jail Monday afternoon. His son Hummam Qader Chowdhury told bdnews24.com authorities informed the family Sunday night that Chowdhury was in good health and would be moved to his prison cell. "My father suffered two heart attacks in the meantime and he's still ailing. The doctors told us that his condition was not yet stable. We are quite worried about his life," said Hummam. Salahuddin had a heart attack while he was detained in Dhaka Central Jail four months ago. He was admitted to the National Heart Diseases Institute and later transferred to ICHRI. At ICHRI, a medical board comprising Prof KMHS Sirajul Haque, Prof M Maksumul Haque, Dr Tamjid Ahmed and Dr Riazul Karim treated Chowdhury. They advised the family to fly him to Singapore for a bypass cardiac surgery. But he was not taken to the city state as jail codes did not permit the transfer. bdnews24.
